Overall, I'm relatively proud of my performance on this assignment. I'm definitely not a good writer, but I think
that this stands out among my previous attempts at a narrative in a good way. It was very challenging to get it
to be four pages, however. I've never been a huge fan of length requirements, and I think it's probably because
I tend to write in a very direct manner. I also understand that being direct isn't always the most optimal way
to tell a story, so I can admit it makes some sense. For things I am specifically proud of, I would say that this
was my best attempt at building tension/suspense in my writing career, so that's nice. As for what I want to
improve on, I think the pacing could use some reworking so I will focus more on that for future assignments.
